Citation.sTitle: Partial molar volumes of organic solutes in water. XXIX. Four 2-alkoxyethanols at temperatures T = (298 K to 573) K and pressures up to 30 MPa
Citation.sAbstract: Densities of dilute aqueous solutions of four 2-alkoxyethanols H-(CH2)n-O-CH2-CH2-OH (n = 1, 2, 3, 4) measured in the temperature range from (298 to 573) K and at pressures up to 30 MPa using an automated flow vibrating-tube densimeter are reported. Standard molar volumes were evaluated from the measured data. The present study is an extension of recent measurements performed at atmospheric pressure in the temperature range from (278 to 343) K. Trends in the present homologous series are evaluated and a comparison with results previously measured for the homologous series of similar solutes (poly(ethylene glycols), glymes) is presented.
